between the two opposing

00:03:44.710 --> 00:03:47.240 align:middle line:90%
forces within our own self.

00:03:47.240 --> 00:03:50.140 align:middle line:84%
And as that occurs, our
nervous system is rewired

00:03:50.140 --> 00:03:52.412 align:middle line:84%
and our heart has
permission to open.

00:03:52.412 --> 00:03:54.120 align:middle line:84%
So the question is,
what allows our heart

00:03:54.120 --> 00:03:56.830 align:middle line:84%
to open, to relax
our nervous system,

00:03:56.830 --> 00:03:59.560 align:middle line:84%
to create a perception
of unity, instead

00:03:59.560 --> 00:04:01.660 align:middle line:90%
of a misperception of division?

00:04:01.660 --> 00:04:05.050 align:middle line:84%
And in my teachings, it is
the loving of our own selves,

00:04:05.050 --> 00:04:09.250 align:middle line:84%
the embracing of our own hearts,
the embracing of the emotions

00:04:09.250 --> 00:04:11.350 align:middle line:90%
that life brings up in us.

00:04:11.350 --> 00:04:13.960 align:middle line:84%
Whether we see it as
us versus them or not,

00:04:13.960 --> 00:04:16.660 align:middle line:84%
it is the
self-responsibility of loving

00:04:16.660 --> 00:04:21.010 align:middle line:84%
what arises in our own self that
allows us to unravel the ego

00:04:21.010 --> 00:04:23.020 align:middle line:84%
and to embody the
light of our soul,

00:04:23.020 --> 00:04:25.300 align:middle line:84%
but in the most
heart-centered way.

00:04:25.300 --> 00:04:28.180 align:middle line:84%
>> So what you're saying
