00:05:53.810 --> 00:05:55.970 align:middle line:84%
whether they act in
a loving way or not.

00:05:55.970 --> 00:05:58.169 align:middle line:84%
Just like with children,
we don't always--

00:05:58.169 --> 00:05:59.960 align:middle line:84%
we don't withhold our
love, because a child

00:05:59.960 --> 00:06:00.830 align:middle line:90%
isn't being loving.

00:06:00.830 --> 00:06:03.440 align:middle line:84%
We love the children
who often act out

00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:05.010 align:middle line:90%
when they crave attention.

00:06:05.010 --> 00:06:08.720 align:middle line:84%
So in the same way, our emotions
are doing the same exact thing.

00:06:08.720 --> 00:06:11.330 align:middle line:84%
And for people who are not in
tune with the emotions that

00:06:11.330 --> 00:06:14.810 align:middle line:84%
need love, we have the
perception of a world around us

00:06:14.810 --> 00:06:18.380 align:middle line:84%
that will do the spectacular
exquisite job of being

00:06:18.380 --> 00:06:21.680 align:middle line:84%
any particular
environment or injustice,

00:06:21.680 --> 00:06:24.470 align:middle line:84%
to bring our attention
to that within us that

00:06:24.470 --> 00:06:26.240 align:middle line:90%
needs that loving attention.

00:06:26.240 --> 00:06:29.340 align:middle line:84%
So we're not trying to
be love instead of fear.

00:06:29.340 --> 00:06:32.450 align:middle line:84%
It's a very old paradigm way
of looking at that shift.

00:06:32.450 --> 00:06:36.680 align:middle line:84%
Instead, we're actually looking
at love is not an emotion.

00:06:36.680 --> 00:06:42.260 align:middle line:84%
Love is that which embraces
the arc of any emotion.

00:06:42.260 --> 00:06:46.310 align:middle line:84%
So love is the attention, the
respect, the companionship,

00:06:46.310 --> 00:06:48.350 align:middle line:84%
and the nurturing
affection that we're

00:06:48.350 --> 00:06:51.110 align:middle line:84%
willing to give
all parts of self,

00:06:51.110 --> 00:06:55.160 align:middle line:84%
knowing full well that any
darkness that lingers within us

00:06:55.160 --> 00:06:58.876 align:middle line:84%
is the light begging
to be recognized.

00:06:58.876 --> 00:07:05.300 align:middle line:84%
>> And so how do we see that
as it connects to really

00:07:05.300 --> 00:07:10.850 align:middle line:84%
if someone is looking for this
pathway to be a path that they

00:07:10.850 --> 00:07:15.620 align:middle line:84%
utilize as one of their
tools in an activism role,

00:07:15.620 --> 00:07:19.430 align:middle line:84%
or in a role that
we can feel that?

00:07:19.430 --> 00:07:24.800 align:middle line:84%
How am I actually actively
helping the world,

00:07:24.800 --> 00:07:27.590 align:middle line:84%
while not engaging
in this paradigm that

00:07:27.590 --> 00:07:31.190 align:middle line:84%
feels that if I'm really
going to be doing something,

00:07:31.190 --> 00:07:34.634 align:middle line:84%
I have to be in
adversity in some way?

00:07:34.634 --> 00:07:36.050 align:middle line:84%
And that's my own
words around it.

00:07:36.050 --> 00:07:38.540 align:middle line:84%
I'd love to hear if that's
kind of your perspective

00:07:38.540 --> 00:07:40.670 align:middle line:84%
or if you have a different
way of looking at it.

00:07:40.670 --> 00:07:40.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, no.

00:07:40.880 --> 00:07:42.110 align:middle line:90%
I would agree with you.

00:07:42.110 --> 00:07:45.726 align:middle line:84%
And I just think specifically
when-- so we talk

00:07:45.726 --> 00:07:46.850 align:middle line:90%
about two different things.

00:07:46.850 --> 00:07:50.300 align:middle line:84%
Sacred activism,
which is external

00:07:50.300 --> 00:07:51.890 align:middle line:84%
empowered decision-making
